yc7gdff4u','香港商用航空中心二号停机库扩建工程(称为三号停机库)','香港商用航空中心二号停机库扩建工程(称为三号停机库)','香港商用航空中心','2011 年 05 月 14 日 - 2012 年 05 月 31 日','<p>此工程是香港商用航空中心二号停机库的扩建工程，座落于二号停机库旁,称为三号停机库。新的三号停机库与现有的停机库相得益彰，提供足够的机库空间以满足香港飞机库不断增长的需求。</p><p>此工程主要包括建造一个有机库门的钢结构停机库（约80米×50米），安装停机库内的钢结构，并提供所有在工场必要的防护油漆涂料，建造一组一层高的辅助工场，停机坪工程，外部铺设道路，工地工程，水管，渠务设施以及机械，通风和空调及电力装置。</p>','2025-05-31 04:27:54.705000','2025-07-07 08:01:12.916000','2025-07-07 08:01:13.893000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(192,'zhdc63qb838vepb2xnvp9bfm','把荔枝角公园游泳池的副池改建为室内暖水池 (合约编号 AL W316)','把荔枝角公园游泳池的副池改建为室内暖水池','建筑署','2010 年 02 月 01 日 - 2012 年 03 月 31 日','<p>政府计划在荔枝角公园游泳池拟建室内暖水游泳设施，措施将有效向该区居民推广冬季游泳可强身健体的讯息， 并提高该游泳池的整体使用率。</p><p>工程包括为副池设置一个轻型遮盖及可伸缩边墙及一个新的热水系统；为有盖行人道提供暖风系统；拆除位于副池毗邻的现有儿童嬉水池和进行更衣室的通风/暖气设施和热水系统的相关改善工程。</p>','2025-05-31 04:30:20.900000','2025-07-07 08:01:13.234000','2025-07-07 08:01:13.936000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(193,'kd6w0r0yfdo2u365uf53mi4q','香港商用航空中心二号停机库建造工程','香港商用航空中心二号停机库建造工程','香港商用航空中心有限公司','2006 年 11 月 14 日 - 2007 年 08 月 15 日','<p>工程主要包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造一个停机库工程，包括地基，钢结构屋顶和上盖建筑，墙壁和屋顶面板，供应及安装机电和屋宇装备。</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>利用钢筋混凝土建造一间单层办公楼，并包括相关的装饰，机电和屋究宇装备安装服务。</li></ul>','2025-05-31 04:51:24.638000','2025-07-07 08:01:13.740000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.092000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(194,'cjfdacxxav0yhdln836kgy1z','Hong Kong International Airport Contract 3501- Antenna Farm and Sewage Pumping Station','Hong Kong International Airport Contract 3501- Antenna Farm and Sewage Pumping Station','Hong Kong Airport Authority','12 June 2017 - 09 August 2018','<p>HKAA is required to relocate the existing antenna farm and one of the existing sewage pumping stations to facilitate the future expansion of Terminal 2.  This project includes the construction of the new antenna farm and sewage pumping station including associated utilities, road works and landscaping.</p><p>The works mainly comprise an antenna farm (including an antenna common equipment building and antenna tower) – complete with ABWF and building services; A sewage pumping station (Pumping</p><p>Station PS 12) – civil and structural engineering works only; Associated airport systems; Associated incoming and outgoing foul and grey water pipes; Associated roadworks, utilities, earth retaining walls and landscaping; Trenchless excavation for sewage rising mains; Associated testing and commissioning works; and All Temporary Works.</p>','2025-05-31 04:20:36.722000','2025-07-07 08:01:13.898000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.254000',8,36,'en'),(195,'agxcotg1o1cwxyejxx3wmobg','Noise Mitigation Measures at Sheung Shui - Stage 1 Works (KCRC Contract No. 1/ICP/2004)','Noise Mitigation Measures at Sheung Shui - Stage 1 Works','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','07 May 2004 - 23 July 2005','<p>The major elements of the Works consisted of the construction of 315metres long noise barriers supported on minipile foundation or RC strip footing.</p>','2025-05-31 05:06:03.030000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.079000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.297000',8,36,'en'),(197,'q8ylg8id4kcfoxht7unfts4o','西北客运大楼及停机坪 (香港机场管理局 合约编号304)','西北客运大楼及停机坪','香港机场管理局','1997 年 09 月 01 日 - 1999 年 12 月 31 日','<p>本项目包括建造香港国际机场西北客运大楼，十一条连接桥及占地十万平方尺的停机坪。为顺利完成本项目，承建商面对许多挑战。由于施工期间，需要确保机场的日常运作不受影响，承建商采取了严格的控制措施，包括管制工人及机械的活动范围等，有效地控制及减低施工期间对机场的影响。除此之外，钢结构构成的客运大楼屋顶也是一个很大的挑战。由于本工程的西北客运大楼是以45度角与主客运大楼交接。因此，钢结构屋顶形成了非常复杂的几何设计，我们采用了先进的测量技术及相关的仪器，成功地完成了组装的任务，确保工程的质量。在钢结构的接驳方法上，我们选择了缧丝接合法以取代焊接法。因为此方法更能符合安装现场的施工环境要求，缩短安装时间。另一方面，也消除了机管局对焊接法产生的火花会影响机场运作的疑虑。</p>','2025-05-31 05:21:32.941000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.146000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.345000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(198,'xu3jo3jxbuby0l9tj8uxsh0k','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University Design and Build Contract for Footbridge Linking Phase 8 Development','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University Design and Build Contract for Footbridge Linking Phase 8 Development','The Hong Kong Polytechnic University','15 June 2015 - 29 August 2019','<p>The major scope of this project comprises the design and construction of a footbridge linking the Main Campus and the Phase 8 development of The Hong Kong Polytechnic University. The footbridge is designed as a steel bow-string arch structure with a main span length of 68m across the entire Chatham Road South. The pedestrian walkway with an overall width of about 7m and its associated sub-structures are hung from the two main arch beams by high-tensioned steel bar. The aesthetic form of the footbridge is designed according to the concept of &quot;Flying Fish&quot; and echoes with the surrounding iconic buildings of the University.</p><p>The works under the project include the design and construction of pile foundation, pile cap, RC lift shaft structures, lift installation, steel footbridge structure and its associated sub- structures, architectural works and finishes, building services works, footbridge connection works involving alternation and addition works to the existing Block Z at Phase 8 development.</p>','2025-05-31 04:25:33.348000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.130000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.370000',8,36,'en'),(199,'fb0oh7ecgbgxrf4to1sp7xv4','Northwest Concourse and Apron Works (AA Contract 304)','Northwest Concourse and Apron Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','01 September 1997 - 31 December 1999','<p>The contract to build the concourse extension, eleven fixed link bridges and 100,000ft². of apron area was awarded to the joint venture between Zen Pacific and Shui On. The project presented a number of challenges, not least the construction of the steel roof. The roof has a particularly complex geometry as the Northwest Concourse branches out from the main building at a 45-degree angle, which gives rise to grids of parallelograms with no right angles. A bolted design was chosen for the roof instead of the welded method used on the main terminal. The method of construction was chosen because it was more economical given the small number of roof modules involved and it improved installation time significantly. In addition, the method addressed the Airport Authority’s concerns over sparks from welding, which might have interfered with the airport’s operation.</p>','2025-05-31 05:22:06.861000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.114000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.395000',8,36,'en'),(200,'f8zqpigz8vd3vxa4fk6pmboz','Lamma Power Station – Foundation and Civil Works for Unit 4 & 5 Retrofit of FGD Plant (Contract No. 06/8005)','Lamma Power Station – Foundation and Civil Works for Unit 4 & 5 Retrofit of FGD Plant','The Hong Kong Electric Co., Ltd.','22 December 2006 - 26 May 2008','<ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Dismantle, modify, re-use the existing hoarding for erection of new hoarding</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Piling, pile caps, substructure and plinths for the FGD equipment</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>A new Electrical &amp; Control Equipment Building incl. E&amp;M works for the FGD equipment</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Drainage diversion work incl. Demolition of Sewage Treatment Plant No. 1 and associated Plant Room for construction of Electrical &amp; Control Equipment Building</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Supporting rack spanning across Main Road for the installation of cables connecting the Electrical &amp; Control Equipment and FGD equipments</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Trenches at Main Road, pits, rack support, plinths, A&amp;A works in electrical equipment room at Common Equipment Area</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Transportation, treatment &amp; disposal of contaminated soil under Unit 4 and 5 Light Oil Tanks &amp; No. 2 Oil Separator</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Civil works for Combines Cycle Plant GT Units 5 &amp; 7</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>A new Fire Services Pump Room and Water Tank incl. E&amp;M works for Electrical &amp; Control Equipment Building</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>No. 2 CW Outfall Foam Suppression System Civil Improvement Works</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Units 3 &amp; 5 Cable Trench Improvement Works</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Provision of planter box at slope tow of Stacker Road</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Confirmatory drilling for reviewing settlement of LMX</li></ul>','2025-05-31 04:45:07.512000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.269000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.502000',8,36,'en'),(201,'skihvbuirl6wqilnaj53xklv','上水隔音设施第一期工程 (九广铁路合约编号：1/ICP/2004)','上水隔音设施第一期工程','九广铁路','2004 年 05 月 07 日 - 2005 年 07 月 23 日','<p>新建一条长315米隔音屏障（可用微型桩筏或钢筋混凝土基础）</p><br/><br/>','2025-05-31 05:06:34.358000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.313000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.530000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(202,'li1ukj18cqdgz0xpgmjyq1q3','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road (Contract No. HY/2003/27)','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road','Highways Department','10 June 2004 - 29 May 2008','<p>One of the most complex and challenging aspects of this project is the temporary traffic arrangements (TTA) while constructing the flyover in the highly congested area of Causeway Bay.</p><br/><p>Numerous traffic simulations analyses are required to study the impact of each TTA scenario. The analyses requires tremendous amount of data to accurately predict the effects of any chosen TTA.</p><br/><p>A 70m long temporary steel off ramp was constructed to maintain the existing traffic flow, with part of the existing flyover initially demolished to allow the construction of the proposed flyover.</p><br/><p>The low soffit level of the proposed flyover with gradients in both directions and the road height clearance requirement coupled with the excessively long span over Victoria Park Road made the design of the falsework decking nearly impossible. The depth of the deck had to meet the various road height clearances, and structural requirements.</p>','2025-05-31 05:04:55.786000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.357000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.574000',8,36,'en'),(203,'i4juf2g2c6fj37l65l2xy6mx','Noise Mitigation Measures at Hong Lok Yuen Section (Contract No. 1/ICP/2000)','Noise Mitigation Measures at Hong Lok Yuen Section','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','01 November 2000 - 07 July 2001','<p>Since the work was carried out during train service hours, a chain link fence had to be erected to separate the live tracks and the work area. Moreover, during construction period, special care had to be taken particularly on erecting structural steel posts and acoustic panels ensuring no object would obstruct the tracks, and no object nor person would come within reach the 2.75m regime of the KCRC’s high voltage equipment in lifting operation.</p><br/><p>The limited access to the work area also made the concreting work difficult and risky as specially long tremie pipe of 400m had to be connected from Hong Lok Yuen Road to the southern end of the Site for casting footing and upstand.</p><br/><p>Part of the site&#x27;s loading / unloading area occupied the road area owned by Hong Lok Yuen(HLY), but since the site was closed to HLY, the project management team had to liaise with the HLY Management Office for permission of road use and settle any complaints raised during construction. Fortunately a harmonious relationship was maintained with the HLYMO and its residents and no complaints were received throughout the construction period.</p>','2025-05-31 05:14:00.619000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.501000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.741000',8,36,'en'),(204,'x6qujacxk3r02na8dloncxug','Expansion of Kiosks and other Facilities at Lok Ma Chau Boundary Crossing, Phase I','Expansion of Kiosks and other Facilities at Lok Ma Chau Boundary Crossing, Phase I','Architectural Services Department, HKSAR','01 March 1999 - 31 December 1999','<p>This is a fast track project for the construction of a large podium at Lok Ma Chau for the cross border traffic. The project included the design and construction of piled foundation systems and the podium, kiosks, structural steel roof canopies and the other associated facilities.</p><br/><p>The extremely busy cross border traffic has bring along immence pressures to the rapid completion of the project. In order to complete the project in the shortest possible time, the Group has deployed huge amount of resources and affort, worked with close co-operations with all concerned parties. Finally, the project was completed on time.</p><br/><p>On the other hands, to mitigate any impact on the extremely busy cross border traffic during the construction was another major challenge</p>','2025-05-31 05:18:09.491000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.569000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.824000',8,36,'en'),(205,'eao9365dtq09urf8wexf4a0k','新界马鞍山九十二区马鞍山综合运动场第一期建造工程 (合约编号：RE G324)','新界马鞍山九十二区马鞍山综合运动场第一期建造工程','建筑署','1998 年 01 月 01 日 - 1999 年 08 月 27 日','<p>运动场包括跑道及足球场，总地盘面积约 42,000平方米。</p><br/><p>建造钢筋混凝土看台和钢结构顶篷及钢制覆盖板。打桩地基面积约长130米x 阔22 米，由顶篷最高点到地面约16.8米。</p><br/><p>第一期体育场馆包括完成一个运动场和看台。</p><br/><p>土壤，地表和地下排水。</p><br/><p>外部工程及附属建筑物。</p><br/><p>屋宇装备安装。</p><br/><p>停车场，花槽，紧急车辆通道，铺砌面，围墙，排水工程</p>','2025-05-31 05:19:41.560000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.609000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.867000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(206,'ml24kj1h48lvhoq1xoq535u5','Noise Mitigation Measures at Peace Avenue and Ho Man Tin Street (KCRC Contract No. 2/ICP/1997)','Noise Mitigation Measures at Peace Avenue and Ho Man Tin Street','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','01 August 1997 - 31 May 1999','<p>Significant restrictions included limited access to the site due to its close proximity to the operating railway and surrounding road network, as well as difficulty in accessing the site due to the topography with 60% of the site located on an elevated fill embankment with slopes up to 38°. The critical concern to ensure there would be no disruption to the railway&#x27;s normal operation presented the biggest challenge to this project.</p>','2025-05-31 05:22:50.679000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.896000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.087000',8,36,'en'),(207,'iqmkco2sdmqyh44rpqpj04i0','昂坪污水处理厂，污水干渠及污水排放管道 (合约编号： DC/2003/01)','昂坪污水处理厂，污水干渠及污水排放管道','渠务署','2003 年 08 月 18 日 - 2006 年 03 月 09 日','<p>前往工地的信道一直为整个项目的最大挑战。由于限制车辆使用东涌道，本项目取得的许可证甚少。同时，因最接近工地的混凝土厂也需要超过一小时的车程，所以，每天混凝土的浇注量，只能限于200立方米。这限制对于工程的进度起了很大的影响。</p><br/><p>污水处理厂内的各座钢筋混凝土结构及建筑物，都呈不规则的形状。因此，虽耍采用特别设计的模板及复杂的临时支撜结构。这也为整个项目带来一定的难度。</p>','2025-05-31 05:08:38.416000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.915000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.152000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(208,'hzdy79wqqlak6vu2ml4srhtr','Noise Mitigation Measures at Wo Liu Hang, Fo Tan (Contract No. 2007-0003)','Noise Mitigation Measures at Wo Liu Hang, Fo Tan','MTR Comporation Limited','17 March 2008 - 31 March 2010','<p>The major element of Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Design, supply &amp; installation of aluminium acoustic panels.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of mini pile foundations, pile caps and retaining walls.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction and/or modification of escape walkways, stairs and exit doors.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Electrical, Mechanical and Fire Services installations at Wo Liu Hang St. &amp; Lok Lo Ha.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Architectural Builder’s Works and Finishes</li></ul>','2025-05-31 04:35:35.198000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.971000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.184000',8,36,'en'),(209,'rol41agpu17ir19aq9qbg6wk','减音措施 -禾寮坑和火炭 (合约编号: 2007-0003)','减音措施 -禾寮坑和火炭','香港铁路有限公司','2008 年 03 月 17 日 - 2010 年 03 月 31 日','<p>工程的主要内容包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>设计，供应及安装铝质吸音板</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造迷你桩地基，桩帽和护土墙</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造或修改逃生通道，楼梯及逃生门</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>在禾寮坑街及落路下安装电器，机械和消防设施</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>装饰及饰面</li></ul><br/>','2025-05-31 04:34:39.602000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.854000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.174000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(210,'enhf2661mh277gn6f904uijp','罗湖站改善工程：一号至三号站台，连接桥及车站大堂 (九广铁路 东铁合约编号：2002-0092)','罗湖站改善工程：一号至三号站台，连接桥及车站大堂','九广铁路公司','2002 年 11 月 18 日 - 2004 年 07 月 30 日','<p>本项目内所有工程，都是在紧贴现有火车路轨旁或在其上进行。而罗湖站连接罗湖关口，为香港通往深圳最重要的通道。每日人流量超过十万人次，而在节日和主要假期，人流更高达每日三十万人次。其繁忙程度，可以想见。为确保铁路、车站以及关口的正常运作，以免影响正常使用的人士，承建商采取了相应的安全操施及安排，其中包括：大量的工程项目改在晚间，即火车服务停止后进行；提供大量而且稳固的栏栅及工台等用来隔开工程进行的范围和火车的服务范围；实施有效的安全工作程序包括路轨守望员等以确保列车及罗湖站的运作不受工程影响。</p>','2025-05-31 05:10:46.142000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.013000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.201000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(211,'quso838l53i2t7g4d1wsnek2','康乐园隔音措施 (九广铁路公司)','康乐园隔音措施','合约编号：1/ICP/2000','2000 年 11 月 01 日 - 2001 年 07 月 07 日','<p>由于施工安排在列车工作时间进行，因此必须先放置铁丝网栏将施工现场的铁轨和工作区隔开。此外，施工期间，在竖立结构钢柱和安装隔音板时要额外注意，确保没有物体误落入铁轨；并且，在起重操作过程中，任何人、任何物体都不能触碰到2.75米高的高电压设备。</p><br/><p>由于对进出施工现场的限制，令混凝土输送出现困难，特别是用作基脚及竖立构件的混凝土要从康乐园路经过400米长水下浇注管送到工地南侧显得更加危险。</p><br/><p>工地与康乐园十分接近，部分装卸货区的道路属康乐园范围。工程需得到康乐园管理处对路面使用的批准及承诺处理施工过程中收到的任何投诉。最后，工程在没有收到任何投诉及与康乐园管理处友好合作关系下顺利完成。</p>','2025-05-31 05:13:23.225000','2025-07-07 08:01:14.925000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.236000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(212,'g6zko008p0v622uk9a0rgi5q','粉岭公路近上水彩园村及粉岭中心的隔音屏障工程 (合约编号：HY/2003/20)','粉岭公路近上水彩园村及粉岭中心的隔音屏障工程','路政署','2004 年 08 月 23 日 - 2006 年 03 月 20 日','<p>该项工程主要包括沿粉岭公路建造约 600米长的直立式隔音屏障及约2400米长的悬臂式隔音屏障。</p>','2025-05-31 04:55:15.008000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.029000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.252000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(213,'pmsodcb4bmzeackf8ponnzvf','Proposed Extension to Hangar Two (also known as “Hangar Three”)','Proposed Extension to Hangar Two (also known as “Hangar Three”)','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre, Ltd.','14 May 2011 - 31 May 2012','<p>The project is the extension of the existing Hangar Two operated by Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre, Ltd, namely as Hangar Three. The new third hangar aimed to complement the existing hangars in providing sufficient hangar spaces to meet the growing demand for aircraft hangars in Hong Kong.</p><p>Major works under the contract include the construction of an air-craft hangar building (approx. 80 m x 50m) with steel structure and metal cladding complete with hangar door, installation of the steel structure of the hangar building and providing all necessary protective painting at the fabrication yard and the construction of a group of one storey ancillary workshops, apron works, external paved roads, site works, plumbing, drainage installations and mechanical, ventilation and air conditioning and electrical installations.</p>','2025-05-31 04:28:45.658000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.157000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.346000',8,36,'en'),(214,'mrq1cx0do92qzc21wfv1bjct','阿联酋钢铁制造厂钢铁整合工程','阿联酋钢铁制造厂钢铁整合工程','General Holding Corporation (GHC)','2007 年 07 月 03 日 - 2008 年 03 月 03 日','<ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>以预制混凝土海堤砖建造60米长之码头及其相关之装置，如：系船柱，引航灯等</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>码头周边的180,000m3之挖泥工程</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>以预制混凝土海堤砖建造系船柱及栈桥</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>制造及架设结构钢栈桥</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>于码头两边建造石护岸墙</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造直径800mm现场浇筑混凝土构件钻孔桩及钢筋混凝土漏斗式地基</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>供应及装置码头上的护栏</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>供应及装置高柱灯</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>供电系统装置</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>道路铺设及相关之街道装置</li></ul>','2025-05-31 04:42:58.681000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.111000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.341000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(215,'i835yp6xt84eqq9heh8l3ksp','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre Main Contract for the construction of the Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre Hangar 2','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre Main Contract for the construction of the Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre Hangar 2','Hong Kong Business Aviation Centre, Ltd.','14 November 2006 - 15 August 2007','<p>Major works consist of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of an air-craft hanger building including foundations, structural steel roof and superstructure, wall and roof claddings, supply and install M&amp;E equipment and Building Services.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of a single storey ancillary office building with RC structure including the associated architectural finishes, M&amp; E and Building Services.</li></ul>','2025-05-31 04:52:07.703000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.314000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.596000',8,36,'en'),(216,'sfzwqsa8xib69jewfggdnsjt','Noise Barriers on Fanling Highway near Choi Yuen Estate and Fanling Centre (Contract No. HY/2003/20)','Noise Barriers on Fanling Highway near Choi Yuen Estate and Fanling Centre','Highways Department','23 August 2004 - 20 March 2006','<p>The major works of this project is to construct approx. 600m long vertical noise barriers and approx. 2400m long cantilever noise barriers along Fanling Highway.</p>','2025-05-31 04:55:54.407000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.484000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.735000',8,36,'en'),(217,'jtjoxv13qsyixohtmfhh6j97','落马洲过关边界第一期 - 收费亭扩建及其它设施','落马洲过关边界第一期 - 收费亭扩建及其它设施','建筑署','1999 年 03 月 01 日 - 1999 年 12 月 31 日','<p>这是一项快速工程。于落马洲兴建一大型过境交通平台。合约包括设计和建造地基系统、过境站、钢结构牌楼及其它配合设施。</p><br/><p>为繁忙的过境交通，尽快完成本项目带来沉重的压力。我司为加速完成任务，作出重大努力，与各有关单位衷诚合作，终于得以最短的时间完成本项目。</p><br/><p>另一方面，在施工期间，尽量避免影响已经相当繁忙的过境交通，也带来一定程度的挑战。</p>','2025-05-31 05:17:39.987000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.604000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.854000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(218,'wxxxwf7ysfh5hd2srmszsm7p','Improvement Works at Lo Wu Station Platforms 1-3, Link Bridge and Concourse Extension (KCRC East Rail Contract No. 2002-0092)','Improvement Works at Lo Wu Station Platforms 1-3, Link Bridge and Concourse Extension','Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation','18 November 2002 - 30 July 2004','<p>The project included the installation of 156 nos. of vertical and raking mini piles with 273mm diameter to support the Concourse Extension of the Lo Wu Station and the Link Bridge linking the Concourse Extension to the existing Platform 1. The length of the piles constructed ranging from 20m to 40m with 5m long socket into Grade III rock. The piling works also included the Pre-Drilling prior to the commencement of the piling works to determine the rock head level and the target founding level. It also included the Proof Drilling subsequent to the completion of the pile installations.</p><p>As all the works have to be carried out immediately next to the live railway tracks and inside the busy Lo Wu Station in full operation, the Contractor has to undertake all the necessary safety measures and arrangement to ensure that the train service and the operation of the Lo Wu Station will not be affected by the construction works.</p>','2025-05-31 05:10:17.911000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.673000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.893000',8,36,'en'),(219,'vg6fxh0q09q2dryv6myakbah','九广铁路减音措施 – 太平道和何文田街 (合约编号：2/ICP/1997)','九广铁路减音措施 – 太平道和何文田街','九广铁路','1997 年 08 月 01 日 - 1999 年 05 月 31 日','<p>由于施工地点非常接近道路网和运营中的铁路且60%的施工现场位于斜坡达38°的高架路堤上，而业主着重要关注的是确保工程施工进行期间要不阻碍铁路正常运行，因此造就工程的最大难度的挑战。</p>','2025-05-31 05:23:20.458000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.704000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.958000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(220,'se68d47krozm5ct0zp5gf341','Retrofitting of Noise Barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridge at Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches (Contract No. HY/2007/08)','Retrofitting of Noise Barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridge at Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches','Highways Department','08 January 2008 - 09 July 2011','<p>The major elements of Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of noise barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridgeat Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Associated structural modification works to existing bridge parapet and utility troughs</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Associated civil, geotechnical traffic aids, road pavement, drainage etc.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Utilities diversion</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Landscaping works</li></ul>','2025-05-31 04:37:15.906000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.706000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.948000',8,36,'en'),(221,'gk4pomknrxk9h3ad75hisyl7','九广铁路九龙塘至大埔沿线减噪音项目 (合约编号：1/ICP/1999)','九广铁路九龙塘至大埔沿线减噪音项目','九广铁路','1999 年 10 月 01 日 - 2001 年 02 月 28 日','<p>在原有路轨上建造2.9公里隔音屏及逃生楼梯，包括微型桩筏基础和相关电气安装和消防设备</p>','2025-05-31 05:15:24.731000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.805000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.995000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(222,'ojma9eh6sum5zdl3eustgdla','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline (Contract No. DC/2003/01)','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline','Drainage Services Department','18 August 2003 - 09 March 2006','<p>Access to the site area was one of the challenging aspects of the project. The maximum daily fresh concrete delivery was restricted to 200 m3 due to the limited number of vehicular permits and the lengthy delivery time of at least one hour from the nearest concrete batching plant. This had a direct impact on the number of construction joints of the structure and the progress of the works.</p><br/><p>The irregular shapes of various reinforced concrete features of the Sewage Treatment Plant require special form work molds and complex false works arrangements.</p>','2025-05-31 05:09:17.647000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.742000','2025-07-07 08:01:16.038000',8,36,'en'),(223,'z013pvzpjwmenu67nzyewq5t','Emirates Steel Factory, Steel Integration Project','Emirates Steel Factory, Steel Integration Project','General Holding Corporation (GHC)','03 July 2007 - 03 March 2008','<p>Construction of a 60m long jetty with precast concrete seawall blocks including the associated quay furniture, dredging in front of and adjacent to the jetty, construction of dolphins and catwalk supports with precast concrete seawall blocks, fabrication and erection of structural steel catwalks supported on dolphins and catwalks supports, construction of rock revetments at both ends of the jetty, construction of the hopper foundations, supply and installation of the high mast lighting, installation of the power supply system and construction of pavement at the quay area.</p>','2025-05-31 04:43:44.455000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.760000','2025-07-07 08:01:16.072000',8,36,'en'),(224,'sut4us1h2pa7i7tv6o8houvg','铜锣湾行车天桥重建及相关的维园道扩阔工程 (合约编号：HY/2003/27)','铜锣湾行车天桥重建及相关的维园道扩阔工程','路政署','2004 年 06 月 10 日 - 2008 年 05 月 29 日','<p>工 程 计 划 包 括:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>拆 卸 现 有 的 铜 锣 湾 行 车 天 桥 和 毗 邻 的 行 人 天 桥 ；</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建 造 一 条 连 接 东 行 的 维 园 道 与 南 行 之 告 士 打 道 的 210 米 长 的 双 线 单 程 行 车 天 桥 ；</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建 造 一 条 横 跨 维 园 道 的 有 盖 行 人 天 桥 ；</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>为 维 园 道 西 行 线 一 条 170 米 长 的 路 段 重 新 定 线 并 扩 阔 为 5 条 行 车 线 ；</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>为 维 园 道 东 行 线 一 条 225 米 长 的 路 段 重 新 定 线 ； 以 及</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>进 行 包 括 环 境 美 化 工 程 之 相 关 工 程 。</li></ul>','2025-05-31 05:04:14.391000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.814000','2025-07-07 08:01:16.081000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(225,'h2ryifurz6bqtvpn1ffl661w','Conversion of the Secondary Pool of the Lai Chi Kok Park Swimming Pool into an Indoor Heated Pool (Contract No. AL W316)','Conversion of the Secondary Pool of the Lai Chi Kok Park Swimming Pool into an Indoor Heated Pool','Architectural Services Department','01 February 2010 - 31 March 2012','<p>Hong Kong Government proposed to build an indoor heated swimming pool, which would have the effect of promoting swimming in winter and better health amongst the residents in the district, and thus enhancing the overall usage of the swimming pool.</p><p>The project includes the provision of a light cover and retractable sidewalls for the secondary pool; a new heating system to the secondary pool and a covered-walkway; demolition of the existing children&#x27;s fun pool and associated improvements to ventilation and hot water systems in changing room.</p>','2025-05-31 04:29:49.879000','2025-07-07 08:01:15.945000','2025-07-07 08:01:16.197000',8,36,'en'),(226,'i4zqbjszaqkwjg2p78rejoaq','香港飞机工程有限公司 - 2号飞机维修库','香港飞机工程有限公司 - 2号飞机维修库','香港飞机工程有限公司','2005 年 11 月 10 日 - 2006 年 12 月 20 日','<p>新建的2号飞机维修库面积超过 1.4万平方米，可同时容纳 2只飞机及1只宽体飞机。维修库将为客户提供新设施，有能力应付目前香港国际机场所有处理的维修和改装工作包括：大型维修，改装，修理和大型维修商用飞机及其部件等。</p><br/><p>新钢制飞机维修库位于1号维修库的东部面临南跑道，工程包括地基测量 170米x 85米(14,450平方米）。合约订明维修库最少净跨度和净高度需为157米（宽）和27米（高）。</p>','2025-05-31 04:53:47.280000','2025-07-07 08:01:16.078000','2025-07-07 08:01:16.396000',8,36,'zh-CN'),(227,'qiyytb7vitbw5ql9jwkitrjy','Contract No. HY/2016/04 Elevated Walkway between Tong Ming Street and Tong Tak Street , Tseung Kwan O','Contract No. HY/2016/04 Elevated Walkway between Tong Ming Street and Tong Tak Street , Tseung Kwan O','Highways Department','30 December 2016 - 03 March 2021','<p>The main purpose of this project is to construct an elevated walkway connecting the existing footbridge across Tong Ming Street to the shopping mall above Tseung Kwan O MTR Station and a lift at the end of the elevated walkway near Tong Tak Street to provide a comfortable and convenient access for residents (especially the elderly) of Tseung Kwan O town centre. The existing cycle parking area at Tong Ming Street is to be reconstructed and expanded to increase the number of cycle parking spaces for use by the residents of the area.</p><br/><p>This contract mainly comprises construction of an elevated walkway of about 180 m in length and about 5 m in clear width, connecting the existing footbridge across Tong Ming Street to the shopping mall above Tseung Kwan O MTR Station; construction of a lift at the end of the proposed elevated walkway near Tong Tak Street; reconstruction and expansion of the existing cycle parking area; and ancillary works, including associated road, drainage, public utilities, public lighting, landscaping, and electrical and mechanical works.</p>','2025-05-31 04:24:10.500000','2025-07-07 08:01:16.195000','2025-07-07 08:01:16.467000',8,36,'en'),(228,'erhz9whfsovv7ix6we5w94x4','Completion of Ma On Shan Sports Complex, Phase I at Area 92, Ma On Shan, N.T. (Contract No. RE G324)','Completion of Ma On Shan Sports Complex, Phase I at Area 92, Ma On Shan, N.T.','Architectural Services Department Government of HKSAR','01 January 1998 - 27 August 1999','<p>A sports field, total site area approx. 42,000 m2 comprising running track, football field.</p><br/><p>Spectator stand with reinforced concrete structure and structural steel canopy with steel sheet cladding and piling foundations approx. 130m x 22m overall on plan and 16.8m high from ground level to the top of steel canopy.</p><br/><p>Completion of a partially completed sports complex comprising a sports field and a spectator stand.</p><br/><p>Soil, surface at er and sub-soil drainage.</p><br/><p>External works and ancillary buildings.</p><br/><p>Building services installation.</p><br/><p>Car park, planter, Emergency Vehicular Access (EVA), paving, fence wall, drainage works</p>','2025-05-31 05:19:09.467000','2025-07-07 08:01:16.402000','2025-07-07 08:01:16.586000',8,36,'en'),(229,'z5gn0xisepnzgvukpohj5vrc','Noise Mitigation Measures at KowloonTong and Tai Po Section (Contract No. 1/ICP/1999)','Noise Mitigation Measures at KowloonTong and Tai Po Section','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','01 October 1999 - 28 February 2001','<p>A construction of a 2.9km low rise noise barrier and escape footpath and stairs along the existing live railway track are to be constructed. The works include mini-pile and raft foundation and associated electrical installation and fire services. </p>','2025-05-31 05:14:52.995000','2025-07-07 08:01:16.425000','2025-07-07 08:01:16.628000',8,36,'en'),(230,'f7us1ma6pdlvuriuf6brzlwd','HAECO Aircraft Maintenance Hangar No. 2 Main Contract Works','HAECO Aircraft Maintenance Hangar No. 2 Main Contract Works','Hong Kong Aircraft Engineering Co., Ltd.','10 November 2005 - 20 December 2006','<p>The construction of the Hangar No. 2 will provide the Client with a new facility in excess of 14,000m2 in area which will be able to accommodate two + one wide-bodied aircraft at one time and will have the capability to undertake all maintenance and modification work currently handled at HKIA including but not limited to: heavy maintenance, modification, repair and overhaul of commercial aircraft and their components.</p><br/><p>The new steel hangar including foundation measured 170mx85m (14,450m2) on plan and is located to the east of the existing Aircraft Maintenance Hangar No. 1 facing the South Runway. The minimum clear span and headroom of the hangar required are 157m (wide) and 27m (high) respectively.</p><br/><br/>','2025-05-31 04:53:07.613000','2025-07-08 08:42:04.751000','2025-07-08 08:42:04.813000',8,31,'en');
